comments.body:
`closingFeeRate ?? 0` shows estimated PnL without closing fees while `usePerpsOrderFees` is loading or on error (`feeRate: undefined`). This briefly displays an inflated number the user could act on.

Fix: add `closingFeeRate === undefined` to the null guard so the PnL row stays hidden until the rate resolves:
```ts
if (!estimatedSize || !takeProfitPrice || !pnlEntryPrice || closingFeeRate === undefined) {
  return null;
}
```
Same applies to the SL memo at line 316. This echoes @geositta's earlier review comment.
